# Environment Variables Template

## Backend (.env)

```
# Django Settings
DEBUG=True
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-change-in-production
ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,127.0.0.1,your-domain.com

# Database
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///db.sqlite3
# For PostgreSQL: postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/dbname

# CORS
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000,https://your-domain.com

# Email Configuration (Optional)
EMAIL_BACKEND=django.core.mail.backends.console.EmailBackend
EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USE_TLS=True
EMAIL_HOST_USER=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD=your-app-password

# SMS Gateway (Optional)
SMS_GATEWAY_API_KEY=your-api-key
SMS_GATEWAY_SENDER_ID=your-sender-id

# Payment Gateway (Optional)
PAYMENT_GATEWAY_KEY=your-payment-key
PAYMENT_GATEWAY_SECRET=your-payment-secret

# Security
SECURE_SSL_REDIRECT=False
SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=False
CSRF_COOKIE_SECURE=False
```

## Frontend (.env.local)

```
# API Configuration
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:8000/api

# Feature Flags
REACT_APP_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=false
REACT_APP_ENABLE_SMS=false
REACT_APP_ENABLE_GPS_TRACKING=false

# Optional: Third-party services
REACT_APP_GOOGLE_MAPS_KEY=your-key
REACT_APP_SENTRY_DSN=your-sentry-dsn
```

## Production Notes

For production deployment:

1. **Backend**
   - Generate a strong SECRET_KEY
   - Set DEBUG=False
   - Update ALLOWED_HOSTS with your domain
   - Use environment-specific database
   - Configure proper email backend
   - Set security flags to True

2. **Frontend**
   - Update API_URL to production backend
   - Enable analytics and monitoring
   - Optimize build size
   - Configure proper error tracking

## Local Development

Copy and modify these templates for your local setup:

```bash
# Backend
cd backend
cp .env.example .env

# Frontend
cd ../frontend
cp .env.example .env.local
```
